content:
Basic Routing

Use Omni-Channel to route work from a channel directly to a queue. For example, you can route calls received from a specific phone channel to a specific queue.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience

Omni-Channel is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Route Chats to a Queue
To route chats, edit the chat button and specify the routing method and queue.

Route Calls to a Queue
To route calls, edit the contact center channel and specify the routing method and queue for the channel.

Route Messages to a Queue
To route messaging sessions, edit the channel and specify the routing method and queue for the channel.
title: Basic Routing in Service Cloud
